cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and image processing, specifically on person re-identification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as learning a linear transformation and a dictionary to encode pixel values, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of color spaces and photometric invariance, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves analyzing and comparing different approaches, which could also place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
